Dataset Description

This project uses the Brazilian E-commerce Public Dataset by Olist, which contains data about orders placed on the Olist marketplace between 2016–2018.

The dataset represents a real e-commerce platform and includes information about:

customer orders

products and sellers

delivery timelines

customer reviews

It allows analysis of the order fulfillment pipeline to identify delivery delays and operational bottlenecks.

Data Source

Source: Kaggle
Dataset: Brazilian E-commerce Public Dataset by Olist

Tables Used

This project uses the following main tables:

orders
Contains order lifecycle timestamps.

Key columns:

order_id
customer_id
order_purchase_timestamp
order_approved_at
order_delivered_carrier_date
order_delivered_customer_date
order_status

order_items
Links orders to products and sellers.

Key columns:

order_id
product_id
seller_id
price
freight_value

customers
Contains customer location information.

Key columns:

customer_id
customer_city
customer_state

products
Contains product catalog information.

Key columns:

product_id
product_category_name

order_reviews
Contains customer feedback for orders.

Key columns:

review_id
order_id
review_score
Analytical Objective

The goal of this project is to analyze the order fulfillment process and identify factors contributing to delivery delays, including seller performance, product category complexity, and regional logistics differences.
